    • Method Detail

      • getCostDataWrapperType

        IType getCostDataWrapperType(CalcRoutineParameterSet paramSet)
        Get the IType of the wrapper that will be used by rate routines for the given parameter set. The RateRoutine editor accesses a CostData instance using this wrapper type. This allows the desired set of CostData-related properties to be shown in "virtual" form. For example, the RateRoutine editor shows "AdjustedRate" rather than StandardAdjRate, OverrideAdjRate and ActualAdjRate. The wrapper implementation maps the value of AdjustedRate to the correct underlying property.
        Parameters:
        paramSet - The parameter set for which the corresponding wrapper type is desired
        Returns:
        the iType corresponding to the instance that makeCostDataWrapper would return if given paramSet.

      • includeProperty

        java.lang.Boolean includeProperty(java.lang.String policyLinePatternCode,
                                  IPropertyInfo prop)
        Filtering function to control whether to include a property. This operates during the traversal of the policy graph, and controls whether a reference from one class to another will be traversed.

        For example, PolicyLocation has a foreign key to an AccountLocation. By default, PolicyLocation.AccountLocation is not traversed. To change this behavior, you might add the condition

        if (prop.OwnersType.isAssignableFrom(entity.PolicyLocation) and prop.Name == "AccountLocation") { return true }

        Note that this function can return one of THREE values:

        • true, if you want this property to be included
        • false, if you want this property to be excluded
        • null, for properties which should retain their default behavior
        It is recommended that this function end with a catch-all "return null" so that any property which is not explicitly handled gets default behavior.
        Parameters:
        policyLinePatternCode - the policy line for which we are doing the graph traversal
        prop - The property descriptor for the reference
        Returns:
        true to include owner.prop; false to exclude it; null to use default behavior

      • getCoverageWrappersForLine

        AvailableCoverageWrapper[] getCoverageWrappersForLine(java.lang.String linePatternCode)
        List of wrapper classes (classes which implement gw.rating.flow.CoverageWrapper) that are applicable to the given line of business. These will be offered to the user as options during parameter set creation.
        Parameters:
        linePatternCode - A string corresponding to a PolicyLinePattern code
        Returns:
        an array of zero or more AvailableCoverageWrapper objects

      • filterIrrelevantItems

        java.util.List<InScopeUsageBase> filterIrrelevantItems(java.util.List<InScopeUsageBase> input,
                                                       java.lang.String policyLinePatternCode)
        This is a postfilter, which RatingEntityGraphTraversal applies to its result set after it has done its introspective traversal on the types. It takes a list of InScopeUsage objects and returns a filtered version of the list. The usages in the input list will all have been derived from the same "root" parameter type.
        Parameters:
        input - a list of InScopeUsageBase instances
        Returns:
        the filtered list of items
